                <head>No. 126.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Fish</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Washburne</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1871-11-20">
                            <hi rend="italic">November</hi> 20, 1871</date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 358.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have to acknowledge the receipt of your
                    dispatch of the 30th ultimo, No. 551, in regard to the protection extended by
                    you to Mexican subjects residing in France, and in reply to state that your
                    action as therein set forth is approved by the Department. You will continue to
                    use your good offices in their behalf if no objection is entertained on the part
                    of the French government.</p>
                <p>I am, &amp;c,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>HAMILTON FISH.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
